Nigerian singer, Simi on Monday revealed that she and her husband, Adekunle Gold do not sing at home as many would think. A Twitter fan, @_eghosa brought up the discussion, saying “I just imagined Simi and Adekunle at home. They’d be singing all over the place”. Responding to tweet, Simi, who wondered why people thought all they do at home is music, said music was not among what they do at home. “Why do people think this?, Simi asked in a tweet. She went further and said, “Lol All we do is watch netflix, touch lips and laugh at people on twitter. Simi and Adekunle Gold, who are both popular Nigerian contemporary music artists, got married earlier this year.